    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <head>[Copy of protest given to the commander of the man-of-war <hi rend="italic"
                        >Aleut</hi>, 12th of August, 1891.]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1891-08-12">August 12, 1891</date>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I, the undersigned, do hereby protest in behalf of the schooner <hi rend="italic"
                        >James Hamilton Lewis</hi> and owners against the illegal seizure of said
                    vessel, her tackling and cargo, and hunting and fishing outfit, by the Russian
                    man-of-war <hi rend="italic">Aleut</hi>, the 2d day of August, 1891, upon the
                    high seas and neutral waters of the ocean. All seal skins on board of said
                    vessel had been killed upon said waters of the ocean with shotguns, and the pup
                    skins on board were taken from the inside of said seal after they were taken on
                    board of the vessel, and no seals were taken on board of the vessel for forty
                    hours previous to the said seizure. I therefore hold the Russian man-of-war <hi
                        rend="italic">Aleut</hi> and her Government responsible for the detention
                    and losses caused by the illegal seizure of said vessel and outfit and
                    cargo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alexander McLean</hi>, <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Master of the Schooner “J. H. Lewis,” of San Francisco,
                            Cal., U. S. A.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
